# Network: Gateway 203.0.113.20 forwards to database 10.1.0.20. Only client
# 192.0.2.10 may use PostgreSQL; every client may use the health-check port.
# Policy: A source-sensitive firewall admits authorized database or health-check traffic.
# Topology: Admitted gateway traffic has its destination rewritten to the database.
# Property authorized-db: The authorized client reaches PostgreSQL.
# Property unauthorized-db: Another client is blocked from PostgreSQL.
# Property health-open: An arbitrary source can reach the health-check service.
# Property authorized-wrong-port: Even the authorized client is blocked on SSH.
# Property client-address-preserved: The firewall and delivery step preserve source IP.
policy = filter(dst_ip = 203.0.113.20 & ((src_ip = 192.0.2.10 & dst_port = 5432) | dst_port = 8080));
topology = filter(dst_ip = 203.0.113.20) . dst_ip <- 10.1.0.20;
check authorized-db: src_ip = 192.0.2.10 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.20 & dst_port = 5432 => dst_ip = 10.1.0.20 & dst_port = 5432;
check unauthorized-db: src_ip = 192.0.2.11 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.20 & dst_port = 5432 => dst_ip = 10.1.0.20;
check health-open: dst_ip = 203.0.113.20 & dst_port = 8080 => dst_ip = 10.1.0.20 & dst_port = 8080;
check authorized-wrong-port: src_ip = 192.0.2.10 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.20 & dst_port = 22 => dst_ip = 10.1.0.20;
check client-address-preserved: src_ip = 198.51.100.200 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.20 & dst_port = 8080 => src_ip = 198.51.100.200 & dst_ip = 10.1.0.20;
